Santander U.K. Plc is planning to
recruit several new directors to boost its board in advance of
possibly selling its shares on the London Stock Exchange, Sky
News  reported , citing people familiar with the company. The U.K.
subsidiary of  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  is also likely to seek a
successor to Chairman Terence Burns, Sky said, citing people
close to the situation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
